api_code = r'''#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
V.E.C.T.O.R Sellable API (Flask)
--------------------------------

This module is intentionally thin. It:
- Authenticates requests via API key
- Applies basic rate limiting + usage metering
- Validates request shape
- Calls the core engine

ENV:
  VECTOR_API_KEYS          Comma-separated list of allowed keys (quick-start)
  VECTOR_API_KEYS_FILE     Optional path to a file with one key per line
  VECTOR_RATE_LIMIT_RPM    Requests per minute per key (default: 60)
  VECTOR_PORT              Default: 8080
  VECTOR_HOST              Default: 0.0.0.0

NOTES:
- For production, swap the in-memory limiter with Redis (drop-in).
- Keep the engine independent: the engine never sees auth/billing details.
